
[1]obstinately

   OB'STINATELY, adv. Stubbornly; pertinaciously; with fixedness of
   purpose not to be shaken, or not without difficulty; as a sinner
   obstinately bent on his own destruction.

   Inflexible to ill and obstinately just.
